cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper discusses a new architecture for single image super-resolution using deep neural networks. This topic falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also introduces an edge difference constraint, which relates to image processing (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of fully connected layers and upsampling weights suggests a neural network approach, which falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
